WEBVTT

00:02.208 --> 00:03.875
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

00:30.166 --> 00:32.708
Today, in what could be
the worst storm

00:32.708 --> 00:35.250
in the history
of our nation's capital!

00:35.250 --> 00:38.833
Hail the size of softballs!
Gale force winds!

00:38.958 --> 00:41.000
Monsoon-like rains!

00:41.000 --> 00:43.875
So far, the National Weather
Service has no explanation

00:43.875 --> 00:46.750
for the sudden
and bizarre nature
of this storm.

00:46.750 --> 00:50.250
It's those freaky mutants, man!
They're doing this!

00:51.250 --> 00:53.083
It never changes.

00:54.708 --> 01:00.416
Whoa! No offense, Cyke,
but I'm about to lose my lunch!

01:00.416 --> 01:03.750
Who do I have to pay
to get off this ride?

01:03.750 --> 01:05.500
[STORM EXCLAIMS IN PAIN]

01:05.500 --> 01:09.083
Something is very wrong!

01:09.333 --> 01:12.458
The sky, the air, the wind!

01:12.458 --> 01:17.375
Injured.
Crying. Not of the Earth!

01:17.375 --> 01:21.333
Take it easy, Storm!
It's just a bumpy ride.

01:26.000 --> 01:29.708
The irregular weather patterns
validate Storm's
intuitive distress.

01:29.708 --> 01:32.875
They defy nature,
in that they do not coincide

01:32.875 --> 01:35.708
with the meteorological
pressure systems that
cause them.

01:35.875 --> 01:37.166
[EXCLAIMS]

01:37.166 --> 01:39.083
[GROANS]

01:39.083 --> 01:44.583
Storm, it's okay! Let me help!
Cyke, please take us down!

01:45.625 --> 01:48.458
Stay back! All of you!

01:49.750 --> 01:51.333
[EMERGENCY HATCH BEEPING]

01:55.000 --> 01:56.750
Storm! No!

01:56.750 --> 01:58.875
She's got to do this, kid!

02:03.416 --> 02:05.416
What's she doing out there?

02:05.416 --> 02:08.583
-Stay with her, Cyke!
-Hold on, everyone!

02:10.083 --> 02:12.583
Find an appropriate
landing area, Cyclops.

02:12.583 --> 02:14.708
The wind shear factor
just tripled!

02:14.708 --> 02:16.625
Forget appropriate!

02:16.625 --> 02:19.375
I just hope we can
get this thing down
in one piece!

02:24.291 --> 02:27.000
Controls won't respond!

02:32.958 --> 02:34.583
[BOTH SCREAMING]

02:40.375 --> 02:42.583
Tell me when the scary part
is over!

02:42.583 --> 02:44.958
Beast! Bypass
auto-landing gear release

02:44.958 --> 02:47.583
and activate reverse thrusters
now!

03:04.875 --> 03:07.958
I command the Sahara winds,

03:08.083 --> 03:12.250
transform this ice to steam!

03:19.375 --> 03:20.708
[WOLVERINE GRUNTING]

03:22.833 --> 03:26.208
As you requested, Jubilee.
The scary part is over.

03:26.208 --> 03:28.125
[ALARM BLARING]

03:32.625 --> 03:34.833
Radical landing.

03:34.833 --> 03:38.458
Yeah, almost looked like
old bug eye knew
what he was doing.

03:38.458 --> 03:42.708
Come in, Storm! Where are you?
Get back here immediately!

03:48.166 --> 03:50.208
This cannot be!

04:07.083 --> 04:12.125
[GROANING] What are you?
I will not allow it!

04:12.750 --> 04:14.708
[GROANING]

04:17.125 --> 04:18.500
[SCREAMING]

04:25.625 --> 04:29.833
Let me go. I must fight it.

04:35.000 --> 04:39.250
The danger has passed.
You are safe now.

04:40.750 --> 04:44.500
Who are you? What are you?

04:44.500 --> 04:48.458
I have traveled across
dimensions
of space to find you.

04:48.458 --> 04:51.583
My name is Arkon,
ruler of Polemachus.

04:52.500 --> 04:54.500
My planet is dying.

04:54.500 --> 04:57.750
You, mistress of the elements,
can save us.

04:57.875 --> 05:00.333
You created this chaos.

05:00.333 --> 05:03.458
It is but a hint of the misery
that afflicts my planet.

05:03.458 --> 05:06.958
With every second,
Polemachus comes closer
to extinction.

05:06.958 --> 05:10.875
How could you endanger
all of these people just
to get to me?

05:10.875 --> 05:12.583
That is barbarous!

05:12.583 --> 05:14.625
My people depend on me.

05:14.625 --> 05:17.583
I must be prepared
to do anything to save them.

05:17.583 --> 05:20.625
Can you and those
of your planet forgive me?

05:22.583 --> 05:24.708
The skies are clear!

05:25.125 --> 05:27.833
Are you hurt? Talk to us!

05:28.500 --> 05:30.166
Where are you?

05:30.875 --> 05:34.875
Oh, no! Cyclops,
do you read me?

05:34.875 --> 05:36.708
[GROANS] Of all the times.

05:36.875 --> 05:39.833
-You must come with me now.
-But I cannot!

05:42.375 --> 05:44.750
Do not make me beg! I need you!

06:01.708 --> 06:02.958
[GASPS]

06:05.375 --> 06:08.708
Sorry, we have sort
of an emergency!

06:12.458 --> 06:13.458
[BEEPING]

06:14.416 --> 06:15.708
Who's "we"?

06:15.708 --> 06:17.291
WOLVERINE:
The Cub Scouts, bub.

06:17.291 --> 06:20.583
-Now move over!
-DRIVER: Uh, sure.

06:25.958 --> 06:28.000
We appreciate your cooperation

06:28.000 --> 06:31.208
and assure you
that you shall be fully
compensated.

06:31.208 --> 06:33.708
[LAUGHING NERVOUSLY]
Anything you say.

06:33.708 --> 06:36.583
Don't worry.
They're not as bad
as they look.

06:39.500 --> 06:42.875
BEAST: Professor,
the meteorological
disturbance is over.

06:42.875 --> 06:44.958
Climatic
and atmospheric conditions
have stabilized.

06:44.958 --> 06:46.166
[COMPUTER BEEPING]

06:46.166 --> 06:47.458
That is excellent news.

06:47.458 --> 06:49.958
But I see that Storm
is not with you.

06:49.958 --> 06:52.833
As you may have deduced,
she left us
to battle the raging elements.

06:52.833 --> 06:55.000
Our attempts to reach her
have failed thus far.

06:55.166 --> 06:57.375
But we've determined
the location of her
communicator

06:57.375 --> 07:00.125
to be near
the Washington Monument,
and are en route.

07:00.125 --> 07:02.583
-Keep me informed.
-Certainly, Professor.

07:02.583 --> 07:04.875
Because if Cerebro cannot
find her,

07:04.875 --> 07:10.083
it means she is thousands
of miles away, unconscious,
or worse.

07:21.166 --> 07:23.250
I found Storm's communicator!

07:24.250 --> 07:27.208
-Any sign of Storm?
-This is most unusual.

07:27.958 --> 07:31.250
Either somebody likes
to play the back nine
at midnight,

07:31.416 --> 07:35.208
or this has something to do
with what happened to Storm.

07:36.583 --> 07:40.166
-XAVIER: Any luck, Beast?
-It is most perplexing,
Professor.

07:40.166 --> 07:43.291
A simple beam of light
can easily pass through it,

07:43.416 --> 07:47.250
yet it completely occludes
the radioactive energy
of an x-ray.

07:47.375 --> 07:50.875
Its matter contains
no recognizable elements.

07:50.875 --> 07:52.708
And, alas, every attempt

07:52.708 --> 07:56.291
to identify its primary energy
source has proved futile.

07:56.500 --> 07:59.458
How much longer
are we gonna play
with that golf ball?

07:59.458 --> 08:03.625
Try to be patient, Jubilee.
Beast is doing the best he can.

08:03.625 --> 08:05.875
I'm afraid we may never
find her.

08:05.875 --> 08:10.500
It's just the last time
we saw Storm,
she was, well, freaking out!

08:10.500 --> 08:13.000
-Something's real wrong.
-The kid's right.

08:13.000 --> 08:15.500
Playing chemistry set
ain't getting us anywhere.

08:15.500 --> 08:17.208
What'd I do?

08:17.208 --> 08:19.875
XAVIER: Your impatience
may have opened a door.

08:19.875 --> 08:21.458
But, to where?

08:21.458 --> 08:24.625
To Storm.
That's why she left it for us.

08:24.625 --> 08:27.416
We cannot be sure she left it.

08:27.416 --> 08:32.375
Send me a postcard when
you're sure. In the meantime,
I'm gonna find out!

08:32.583 --> 08:33.833
Come on!

08:34.000 --> 08:36.875
Logic is on Logan's side.
Shall we?

08:36.875 --> 08:38.250
Let's go!

08:40.875 --> 08:43.291
Into the unknown.

09:01.166 --> 09:04.708
Why did you deny me the chance
to speak to my friends?

09:04.708 --> 09:09.208
If your need is just,
why drag me here like
a prisoner?

09:09.208 --> 09:10.625
Forgive me, Storm.

09:11.625 --> 09:13.875
Your friends may have tried
to dissuade you.

09:13.875 --> 09:17.583
Please understand,
it was the action
of a desperate man.

09:18.291 --> 09:22.583
So many lives depend on me.
Every solution
I have tried has failed.

09:22.750 --> 09:26.458
You have saved so many
with your powers and
compassion.

09:26.583 --> 09:29.208
When you cast your eyes
on my troubled world,

09:29.208 --> 09:31.458
you will begin to understand.

09:32.125 --> 09:36.583
My people huddle,
sheltered the best they can.

09:36.583 --> 09:39.708
I do not know
how long we can hold out.

09:39.708 --> 09:41.958
These storms have weakened
the Ring of Verdon,

09:41.958 --> 09:45.583
which protects our planet
the way the ozone layer
protects your Earth.

09:45.583 --> 09:51.000
I sense a terrible wound,
even a dying of the planet.

09:53.875 --> 09:58.583
Not only
is our planet suffering,
but so are her inhabitants.

09:59.625 --> 10:02.583
The fluctuating atmosphere
has made my people ill.

10:02.583 --> 10:03.750
[COUGHING]

10:03.750 --> 10:05.500
Can you forgive me now, Storm?

10:05.500 --> 10:08.708
Now that you understand
my responsibilities.

10:08.708 --> 10:12.375
Will you, weather goddess,
help my people?

10:13.416 --> 10:14.500
Yes.

10:18.708 --> 10:20.500
[JUBILEE EXCLAIMS]

10:21.333 --> 10:24.500
-We're back
in hurricane central!
-Fascinating!

10:24.500 --> 10:26.125
The base
of a hurricane circulates

10:26.125 --> 10:29.000
in the opposite direction
from its apex.

10:29.000 --> 10:32.416
Is that like worse
than regular hurricanes?

10:33.166 --> 10:35.583
-MAN 1: Intruders!
-WOLVERINE: Hmm.

10:35.583 --> 10:38.500
MAN 2: You will pay for
bringing the plagues and storms

10:38.500 --> 10:41.000
that are destroying our planet!

10:41.000 --> 10:42.750
[CROWD CLAMORING]

10:45.291 --> 10:47.625
Perhaps these visitors
can help us.

10:47.625 --> 10:50.583
How dare you speak out!
Get back to work.

10:50.583 --> 10:53.458
We have nothing to do
with your misfortunes.

10:53.458 --> 10:56.583
We just arrived,
in search of a missing friend.

10:56.583 --> 10:59.500
Yeah,
you welcome wagon ladies seen

10:59.500 --> 11:01.250
a white-haired woman
flying around?

11:01.250 --> 11:03.375
-Get them!
-Stop!

11:05.125 --> 11:09.166
Sorry, but can't we, like,
talk this thing out?

11:09.166 --> 11:12.208
It would behoove you
to turn around, Jubilee.

11:14.250 --> 11:17.250
Are you guys sure
we're not still on Earth?

11:19.000 --> 11:20.708
MAN: Let's get out of here!

11:20.708 --> 11:22.125
[WOMAN SCREAMING]

11:22.958 --> 11:25.083
Why is nothing happening?

11:31.583 --> 11:33.583
STORM: Please be patient.

11:33.583 --> 11:37.458
Getting in tune with an entire
planet takes time and I...

11:37.458 --> 11:39.000
What? What is it?

11:39.000 --> 11:42.208
I am sensing strong
interference.

11:43.833 --> 11:47.750
It is coming from over there.
What is that device?

11:47.750 --> 11:49.375
That is what's keeping this
planet functioning

11:49.375 --> 11:51.166
during this time of crisis.

11:51.166 --> 11:53.333
It is the central energy
transmitter.

11:53.333 --> 11:57.166
Polemachus depends on it
for a great deal,
including our security.

11:57.166 --> 12:00.000
But, Arkon, it is causing...

12:00.000 --> 12:03.166
Surely your powers
are strong enough
to accommodate its presence.

12:03.166 --> 12:05.250
The truth is,
I cannot be sure

12:05.250 --> 12:07.583
that I can help your planet
at all.

12:07.583 --> 12:10.875
Dear Storm,
if your powers have

12:10.875 --> 12:13.166
half the strength
of your compassion,

12:13.166 --> 12:15.458
you can save galaxies.

12:15.958 --> 12:21.708
Take my hand.
I know that together
we will triumph.

12:25.125 --> 12:28.458
Something tells me,
these guys don't want to talk.

12:30.583 --> 12:31.958
[BOTH SCREAMING]

12:32.500 --> 12:33.750
[GROANING]

12:34.208 --> 12:35.416
Cyke!

12:35.833 --> 12:36.958
Hey!

12:36.958 --> 12:38.000
[JUBILEE GRUNTS]

12:38.000 --> 12:39.875
Thanks. I think.

12:41.000 --> 12:44.708
Watch it, boys.
I'm an old hand at this.

12:47.500 --> 12:48.708
[GROANING]

12:49.000 --> 12:50.166
[YELLING]

12:52.250 --> 12:55.833
This is not how I would have
wished to learn about
this new culture.

12:55.833 --> 12:57.000
[GROANS]

13:01.375 --> 13:04.458
The tin cans on this planet
take dancing lessons.

13:04.458 --> 13:07.708
Their center of gravity,
however, is problematic.

13:13.333 --> 13:16.750
I'm so glad we had
this little heart-to-heart.

13:23.083 --> 13:27.500
Scouring sands,
surrender to your deserts.

13:34.833 --> 13:39.208
Tortured skies,
breathe gentle and clear!

13:41.708 --> 13:45.625
Hurricane winds,
punish no more!

13:48.458 --> 13:50.250
[GROANS]

13:50.250 --> 13:55.125
Floods of destruction,
calm your surging struggle!

13:58.333 --> 14:02.583
Forces of life,
heal your wounds!

14:02.583 --> 14:08.083
Shine! Shine,
with strength reborn!

14:14.000 --> 14:17.083
I hope they weren't
from the Chamber of Commerce.

14:17.083 --> 14:20.875
If we perform
an analysis based on
our coordinates of entry,

14:20.875 --> 14:23.125
we may be able
to determine Storm's.

14:23.458 --> 14:25.333
I say,

14:25.333 --> 14:27.750
if a guy was enough
of a big shot
to kidnap Storm,

14:27.750 --> 14:29.625
I bet he lives up there.

14:29.625 --> 14:33.708
Not particularly scientific,
but persuasive nonetheless.

14:33.708 --> 14:35.208
I thought so!

14:42.708 --> 14:44.166
Take cover!

14:47.166 --> 14:49.000
[ALL EXCLAIMING]

14:50.250 --> 14:55.208
Jail! I can't believe this!
It's worse than Earth!

14:55.208 --> 14:58.166
I would exercise
extreme caution, Jubilee.

14:58.166 --> 15:01.000
We have to find a way
to distract our jailers.

15:01.000 --> 15:03.083
Just like in the movies.

15:03.625 --> 15:06.250
This hurts me more than
it's gonna hurt you, pal.

15:07.000 --> 15:08.291
-Traitor!
-Huh?

15:15.458 --> 15:19.000
It's working! Storm!

15:19.000 --> 15:22.416
Must concentrate.

15:22.416 --> 15:27.291
It is over, my darling.
We are saved!

15:28.000 --> 15:29.166
What?

15:33.583 --> 15:36.333
Nice dump, for a kidnapper.

15:37.000 --> 15:38.250
Storm!

15:39.875 --> 15:41.333
Keep away!

15:41.750 --> 15:43.250
Fat chance!

15:43.875 --> 15:45.500
[BOTH GRUNTING]

15:48.125 --> 15:49.208
[EXCLAIMS]

15:49.333 --> 15:51.708
You do not understand!

15:51.708 --> 15:53.000
[GROANS]

15:53.708 --> 15:55.083
[ARKON YELLS]

15:56.583 --> 15:58.958
Storm! Are you all right?

15:58.958 --> 16:03.250
No! Don't! No!

16:28.166 --> 16:30.208
[GROANS]

16:30.208 --> 16:33.458
We don't like our friends
to be yanked off the planet,
pal.

16:33.458 --> 16:36.125
Chasing around the galaxy
ruins my mood!

16:36.250 --> 16:40.083
Stop! Stop! I am here to help.

16:40.083 --> 16:44.458
And unless I am allowed to,
the entire planet will die.

16:44.458 --> 16:47.625
-What?
-Let him go!

16:48.875 --> 16:51.250
Accept our apologies, Storm.

16:51.250 --> 16:54.166
You must realize that
when we lost contact with you,

16:54.166 --> 16:56.375
we feared your life was
in jeopardy.

16:56.375 --> 16:58.458
Is there still time, Storm?

16:58.458 --> 17:01.958
I shall try.
But there cannot be
anymore interruptions!

17:13.083 --> 17:16.708
You will prevail.
I know you will.

17:17.333 --> 17:19.958
Well, guess they don't
need us at all.

17:26.708 --> 17:28.583
[EXCLAIMING]

17:29.458 --> 17:31.458
We are saved!

17:31.458 --> 17:33.000
[ALL CHEERING]

17:35.583 --> 17:40.125
ARKON: Storm, with
self-sacrifice
and incredible will,

17:40.125 --> 17:43.166
you have saved Polemachus!

17:43.166 --> 17:46.750
Now, her people
would like to thank you.

17:46.875 --> 17:51.000
ALL: Storm! Storm! Storm!

17:51.375 --> 17:53.583
Wow! Do you hear that?

17:53.708 --> 17:57.166
Indeed. Storm is most deserving
of their praise.

17:57.458 --> 17:59.708
-Right, but...
-But what?

17:59.708 --> 18:03.208
How long are we gonna have to
hang out here
on the party planet?

18:03.208 --> 18:04.750
JUBILEE: Party pooper.

18:04.750 --> 18:07.458
Wolverine's right.
We have no mission here.

18:07.458 --> 18:09.708
We must at least get word
to the Professor.

18:09.708 --> 18:11.750
[JUBILEE SIGHS]

18:11.750 --> 18:15.875
Ah, but look,
I think that Arkon guy
really likes Storm!

18:15.875 --> 18:17.875
Storm,
I don't know how Earth

18:17.875 --> 18:20.000
celebrates your
incredible deeds.

18:20.000 --> 18:24.750
But I tell you, Polemachus
will love and worship you
now and forever.

18:25.708 --> 18:27.375
And so will I.

18:27.375 --> 18:30.208
No one has ever done for me
what you have.

18:30.208 --> 18:34.250
Arkon, please.
You must not speak this way.

18:34.250 --> 18:37.833
Your courage and love
have given my people
back to me.

18:38.000 --> 18:41.583
-Your beauty has stolen
my heart.
-Arkon, I...

18:41.583 --> 18:45.708
Storm, will you rule by my side
as empress?

18:46.250 --> 18:50.083
Will you bond with me
as you have bonded
with the planet?

18:50.333 --> 18:54.000
Arkon, it is too sudden!

18:54.458 --> 18:57.333
You cannot expect me
to know so soon!

18:57.833 --> 19:00.833
I have known since
the instant we met.

19:01.708 --> 19:07.083
I... Yes! Yes, I will!

19:08.000 --> 19:09.625
[CROWD CHEERING]

19:09.958 --> 19:11.166
Oh, my!

19:14.000 --> 19:19.166
I present to you,
our queen, Storm!

19:19.333 --> 19:21.375
[ALL CHEERING]

19:32.000 --> 19:33.708
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]
